The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 January is 34,923 (4,042.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 January, there were 3,114 new confirmed cases (360.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 January, there were 4,480 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (1,366 fewer cases).
